[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1015},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":990,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":999},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20240321\u002F3544397426\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":974,"date":975,"description":976,"extension":977,"lang":978,"meta":979,"navigation":407,"path":980,"readingMinutes":981,"seo":982,"standalone":983,"stem":984,"tags":985,"tldr":987,"updated":975,"url":988,"__hash__":989},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates.md","Update Your Project Packages with npm-check-updates","5443974261",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":967},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,52,55,94,101,104,119,135,138,145,148,158,164,170,207,217,223,235,238,244,247,261,268,272,281,287,442,453,477,486,869,875,916,919,933,938,941,945,954,963],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Honestly, updating packages on an old project is a massive pain. So here's how to update versions in package.json.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"updating-npm-packages","Updating npm packages",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"Every now and then we update the packages in a project — for new features, bug fixes, or because we need to upgrade Node.js. For me, Node.js upgrades come up often. When you run ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"npm install [package name]",", it installs the version matching your current Node.js. So when you bump Node.js, the package versions follow. At that point you need to update versions in package.json.",[33,34,37],"callout",{"title":35,"type":36},"Note","note",[17,38,39,40,47,48,51],{},"I'll use a project I built before — \"",[41,42,46],"a",{"href":43,"rel":44},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhexschool\u002Fweb-layout-training-gulp",[45],"nofollow","web-layout-training-gulp","\" — as the demo, on the ",[28,49,50],{},"feature\u002Fbs5"," branch. This project was created under Node.js 11.7.0.",[17,53,54],{},"You usually don't jump straight from an old Node.js to the latest — you take it in steps. For this project, Node.js 14 is a reasonable target, so:",[56,57,62],"pre",{"className":58,"code":59,"language":60,"meta":61,"style":61},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","nvm use 14 # switch to Node.js 14\nnpm install\n","bash","",[28,63,64,85],{"__ignoreMap":61},[65,66,69,73,77,81],"span",{"class":67,"line":68},"line",1,[65,70,72],{"class":71},"smYoP","nvm",[65,74,76],{"class":75},"sWayO"," use",[65,78,80],{"class":79},"stw71"," 14",[65,82,84],{"class":83},"sGBqm"," # switch to Node.js 14\n",[65,86,88,91],{"class":67,"line":87},2,[65,89,90],{"class":71},"npm",[65,92,93],{"class":75}," install\n",[17,95,96,97,100],{},"After that, running ",[28,98,99],{},"gulp"," should work fine.",[17,102,103],{},"With the project running on Node.js 14, we're ready to update packages. First, try:",[56,105,107],{"className":58,"code":106,"language":60,"meta":61,"style":61},"npm update --save\n",[28,108,109],{"__ignoreMap":61},[65,110,111,113,116],{"class":67,"line":68},[65,112,90],{"class":71},[65,114,115],{"class":75}," update",[65,117,118],{"class":79}," --save\n",[33,120,121],{"title":35,"type":36},[17,122,123,124,127,128,131,132,134],{},"Just running ",[28,125,126],{},"npm update"," without ",[28,129,130],{},"--save"," won't actually update versions in package.json. Don't forget ",[28,133,130],{},".",[17,136,137],{},"Now versions in package.json are updated.",[17,139,140],{},[141,142],"img",{"alt":143,"src":144},"Package update","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%9B%B4%E6%96%B0%20npm\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-03-21%2011.13.35.png",[12,146,147],{"id":147},"npm-check-updates",[17,149,150,151,154,155,157],{},"You might be wondering — if ",[28,152,153],{},"npm update --save"," already updates packages, why bother with ",[28,156,147],{},"?",[17,159,160,161,163],{},"If you look carefully at your packages, you'll notice many didn't actually update. How do we know? That's where ",[28,162,147],{}," comes in — it checks whether your packages have new versions and updates the versions in package.json.",[17,165,166,167,169],{},"First, install ",[28,168,147],{},". Two options:",[56,171,173],{"className":58,"code":172,"language":60,"meta":61,"style":61},"npm install -g npm-check-updates # global install\n# or\nnpx npm-check-updates # use via npx\n",[28,174,175,191,196],{"__ignoreMap":61},[65,176,177,179,182,185,188],{"class":67,"line":68},[65,178,90],{"class":71},[65,180,181],{"class":75}," install",[65,183,184],{"class":79}," -g",[65,186,187],{"class":75}," npm-check-updates",[65,189,190],{"class":83}," # global install\n",[65,192,193],{"class":67,"line":87},[65,194,195],{"class":83},"# or\n",[65,197,199,202,204],{"class":67,"line":198},3,[65,200,201],{"class":71},"npx",[65,203,187],{"class":75},[65,205,206],{"class":83}," # use via npx\n",[33,208,209],{"title":35,"type":36},[17,210,211,213,214,216],{},[28,212,201],{}," lets you use ",[28,215,147],{}," without installing it globally.",[17,218,219,220,222],{},"I'll demo with ",[28,221,201],{}," directly:",[56,224,226],{"className":58,"code":225,"language":60,"meta":61,"style":61},"npx npm-check-updates\n",[28,227,228],{"__ignoreMap":61},[65,229,230,232],{"class":67,"line":68},[65,231,201],{"class":71},[65,233,234],{"class":75}," npm-check-updates\n",[17,236,237],{},"After running this, you'll see a whole bunch of packages that weren't updated...",[17,239,240],{},[141,241],{"alt":242,"src":243},"Update list","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%9B%B4%E6%96%B0%20npm\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-03-21%2011.18.20.png",[17,245,246],{},"Then run this to check for new versions and update package.json:",[56,248,250],{"className":58,"code":249,"language":60,"meta":61,"style":61},"npx npm-check-updates -u\n",[28,251,252],{"__ignoreMap":61},[65,253,254,256,258],{"class":67,"line":68},[65,255,201],{"class":71},[65,257,187],{"class":75},[65,259,260],{"class":79}," -u\n",[17,262,263,264,267],{},"Don't forget to run ",[28,265,266],{},"npm install"," after to install the new versions. Your project will then be on the latest packages.",[12,269,271],{"id":270},"fixing-gulp-errors","Fixing Gulp errors",[17,273,274,275,277,278,280],{},"Next, fix some errors. After ",[28,276,266],{},", running ",[28,279,99],{}," throws:",[17,282,283],{},[141,284],{"alt":285,"src":286},"Error","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%9B%B4%E6%96%B0%20npm\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-03-21%2011.23.16.png",[56,288,290],{"className":58,"code":289,"language":60,"meta":61,"style":61},"Error in plugin \"gulp-sass\"\nMessage:\n    \ngulp-sass no longer has a default Sass compiler; please set one yourself.\nBoth the \"sass\" and \"node-sass\" packages are permitted.\nFor example, in your gulpfile:\n\n  const sass = require('gulp-sass')(require('sass'));\n",[28,291,292,305,310,316,358,385,402,409],{"__ignoreMap":61},[65,293,294,296,299,302],{"class":67,"line":68},[65,295,285],{"class":71},[65,297,298],{"class":75}," in",[65,300,301],{"class":75}," plugin",[65,303,304],{"class":75}," \"gulp-sass\"\n",[65,306,307],{"class":67,"line":87},[65,308,309],{"class":71},"Message:\n",[65,311,312],{"class":67,"line":198},[65,313,315],{"class":314},"s8XSl","    \n",[65,317,319,322,325,328,331,334,337,340,343,346,349,352,355],{"class":67,"line":318},4,[65,320,321],{"class":71},"gulp-sass",[65,323,324],{"class":75}," no",[65,326,327],{"c